---
title: Third-party Asset Integration
description: Integrating third-party asset providers into the Payap wallet via Centrapay
nav:
  path: Payap
  order: 1
---

By integrating with Payap as a third-party asset provider, your users will be able to connect their loyalty account to their Payap wallet, view their balance, and spend their points at participating merchants on the Centrapay network.

## Connecting an Account
Users connect their asset to Payap via the OAuth 2.0 authorization code flow. You will need to provide an authorization endpoint, token endpoint, and your supported scopes.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant Asset Program Owner
  participant Payap
  participant Payap Backend
  participant Centrapay
  participant Third Party

  Asset Program Owner->>Centrapay: POST /api/asset-types to create a new asset type for the third party
  Centrapay-->>Asset Program Owner: New asset type created
  Payap->>Payap Backend: POST /api/consents to create a consent request to connect to third party
  Payap Backend-->>Payap: Consent returned with authorization url
  Payap-->>Third Party: User visits authorization url to authorize the connection request
  note over Third Party: User approves the connection request
  Third Party-->>Payap: User is redirected back to payap with a authorization code
  Payap->>Payap Backend: POST /api/consents/:id/authorize to exchange the authorization code for tokens
  Payap Backend->>Third Party: POST /token endpoint to exchange the authorization code for tokens
  Third Party-->>Payap Backend: Access and refresh tokens returned
  Payap Backend->>Third Party: List all the assets the user has authorized
  Third Party-->>Payap Backend: Third party assets returned
  loop for each third party asset
      Payap Backend->>Centrapay: POST /api/internal/assets to create a third party asset
      Centrapay-->>Payap Backend: Asset created
  end
  Payap Backend-->>Payap: Authorization successful
```

## OAuth 2.0 Requirements
You must implement the standard OAuth 2.0 authorization code flow. Refresh tokens must be long-lived, as Payap will use them to maintain access without requiring the user to re-authenticate.

- Authorization endpoint URL
- Token endpoint URL
- Supported scopes
- Long-lived refresh tokens
- Token revocation endpoint

### Authorization Request
Payap initiates the connection by redirecting the user to your authorization endpoint with the following parameters:

```bash {% title="Authorization Request" %}
GET https://your.domain/authorize?
  response_type=code
  &client_id=payap
  &redirect_uri=https://service.payap.com/callback
  &scope={requestedScopes}
```

Your authorization endpoint must:

- Validate the request (client ID, redirect URI, and scopes).
- Present your login and consent UI so the user can authenticate and approve the requested scopes.

Once the user has authenticated and consented, redirect them back to Payap's `redirect_uri` with an authorization code:

```http {% title="Redirect Back Example" %}
HTTP/1.1 302 Found
Location: https://service.payap.com/callback?code=SplxlOBeZQQYbYS6WxSbIA&state=xyz123
```

### Token Exchange
Payap will exchange the authorization code for tokens by calling your token endpoint:

```bash {% title="Token Request" %}
curl -X POST https://your.domain/token \
  -H "Authorization: ${jwt}" \
  -d "grant_type=authorization_code" \
  -d "code=SplxlOBeZQQYbYS6WxSbIA"
```

Your token endpoint must validate the authorization code and JWT, then return an access token and a long-lived refresh token:

```json {% title="Token Response" %}
{
  "access_token": "2YotnFZFEjr1zCsicMWpAA",
  "expires_in": 3600,
  "refresh_token": "tGzv3JOkF0XG5Qx2TlKWIA"
}
```

Payap stores the access and refresh tokens securely on its backend. The refresh token must be long-lived, as Payap will use it to maintain access without requiring the user to re-authenticate.

## Asset Type Definition
Before users can connect, an asset type must be registered to identify your loyalty program as a payment method. You must define a namespace and description.

|    Field    |  Type  |                             Description                             |   Examples    |
| ----------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------- |
| name        | String | A name used for uniquely identifying the asset as a payment method. | payap-example |
| description | String | A short human readable description.                                 | Payap Points  |

## Fetching Assets
Your assets are fetched live each time a user opens their Payap wallet. If your system is unavailable, Payap will display a loading error state to the user.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant Payap
  participant Payap Backend
  participant Third Party

  Payap->>Payap Backend: GET /api/assets to list assets
  Payap Backend-->>Payap: Assets returned
  Payap->>Payap Backend: GET /api/assets/:id/balance
  Payap Backend->>Third Party: GET /api/assets/:id
  Third Party-->>Payap Backend: Asset information returned
  Payap Backend-->>Payap: Balance returned
```

### List Assets Endpoint
You must implement a list endpoint that returns all assets the user has authorized. Payap will call this endpoint after the OAuth flow is completed to create an asset in the user's wallet for each one returned.

#### Response

|     Field     |                     Description                     |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| `assetId`     | A unique ID for the asset                           |
| `accountId`   | A unique ID for the user's account on your system   |
| `pointsLabel` | Display label for the points currency e.g. "points" |

### Get Asset Endpoint
You must implement a get asset endpoint that returns the information about the asset with it's current balance. Payap will call this endpoint each time the user opens their wallet, using the `assetId` returned from the list endpoint to identify the user's account.

#### Response
|   Field   |                            Description                             |
| --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `balance` | Current balance in the user's account in the smallest denomination |

